comment.text: Ba Xuyen is like when you&#39;re on a game show and your prize is a Pub. Complete with beer on tap and a rowdy Friday night crowd. Now that&#39;s what I call a &#34;Bar Win.&#34;<br><br>I think the Bahn Mi here is pretty good, but when you&#39;re comparing it to the best of the best (which for me so far is one in San Francisco, and even more so, Nam Nam of Brooklyn), you&#39;re going to end up disappointed by comparison.<br><br>Still, this is tasty, it&#39;s on nice crusty bread, it&#39;s well done. I think it&#39;s the meat that doesn&#39;t come close to Nam Nam, or maybe it&#39;s just everything put together. I can&#39;t tell.<br><br>So, in conclusion... a perfectly passable Bahn Mi. Good, but not great. 4 star, but not 5. Try it, but absolutely do not miss Nam Nam because I think you might come to the same conclusion as I did.<br><br>And if you want to sing while you crunch your way through the Bahn Mi, just sing &#34;Ba Ba black sheep, have you any Xuyen?&#34;

Quick apology to all the previous banh mis I&#39;ve eaten before this review, but Ba Xuyen&#39;s classic #1 is the best sandwich (that&#39;s right, not just banh mi) I&#39;ve ever experienced. Layered with pickled carrot and daikon strips, cucumber, head cheese, pate, barbecued pork, ham, and mayonnaise, it&#39;s a perfectly-crafted work of art for all these sweet, sour, savory, and gamey flavors to fit into a just-toasted baguette. Did I mention that this is all for $6? <br><br>This is a small takeout spot that accepts cash only!

comment.text: I&#39;m not in Sunset Park often, so when I happened to be nearby and saw this as one of my saves places in Yelp I knew I had to stop. $6 for their original bahn mi and $2.75 for a lemon iced tea. Both delicious! I&#39;ve heard this was one of the best bahn mi in the city and it didnt disappoint. Quick takeaway option in the neighborhood that I highly recommend.

photos.caption: Original bahn mi

comment.text: This is the best Banh Mi I&#39;ve had on the east coast. It is truly legit. The bread is so soft and crispy, all of the cold cuts have a perfect texture that is easy to bite and still has pop. Everything just melds together perfectly. <br><br>One of the only legit Banh Mi places in NY (that isn&#39;t just filled with ground pork) and also just happens to be the most legit Banh Mi I&#39;ve had stateside. I grew up eating a LOT of Banh Mi in the Seven Corners/D.C. area and I still think Ba Xuyen takes the cake.<br><br>If you have never had Vietnamese smoothies before, DONT SKIP the Sinh To here. Vietnamese smoothies use fresh fruit and are mindblowingly good. <br><br>Another secret is that the Hu Tieu here (seafood noodle soup) is totally legit and has that deep savory flavor that can be hard to find anywhere outside of Vietnam.<br><br>I used to live in Sunset but now that I don&#39;t anymore, I drive down here sometimes just to pick up 5 sandwiches and a smoothie. If you&#39;re down to watch the sunset in the park, nothing&#39;s better than a sandwich and a cold smoothie to drink along with it.<br><br>P.S. this place is definitely vietnamese owned and the owners/staff are super sweet and chill. I&#39;ve been repping this place for years and so glad I&#39;m finally getting around to leaving a yelp review for them. Thanks Ba Xuyen for existing.

I can&#39;t believe how hard it is to find a Vietnamese deli in NYC and while this not quite it, this is the closest thing I think I&#39;ll find to one.<br><br>Excellent banh beo and the sandwiches were quite nice as well. They even sold moon cakes during the autumn festival.<br><br>Lots of very traditional Vietnamese items. None of them are particularly amazing but the fact that they are made traditionally is so rare that it&#39;s worth a stop to hit the craving.

Photo of Ba Xuyen - Brooklyn, NY, United States

comment.text: I haven&#39;t seen $6 banh mi in yearssss. Now I&#39;m accustomed to paying $8 for a classic, so this steal hit my wallet considerately (though I wouldn&#39;t say it was bursting with meat). Plus, this is some juicy banh mi!<br><br>Classic #1: bread is super soft and the meat juices trickled down my chin after every bite. The meat slices are semi-thick cut (at least thicker than the ones I&#39;ve had in Chinatown), and pickled carrots aren&#39;t as tart (yay!).<br><br>Grilled Pork Banh Mi #8: not your classic grilled pork because these are more chunky pieces than a slab of thinly grilled pork chop at other places.  Definitely tasted the lemongrass, wasn&#39;t too salty, but I can see where people would call this a little bland. Moist meat though!

comment.text: Came here on 7/25 after haircut with hubby for lunch. <br><br>We were very happy that the shop reopen as we&#39;ve been wanting some banh mi sandwich for the longest time! <br><br>We ordered:<br>2 number 1- Banh Mi Pate Thit Nguoi (ham, head cheese, pork roll, pork teriyaki &amp; bbq with pate &amp; butter)<br>and #8- Banh Mi Thit Nuong (Grilled pork with pate &amp; butter- made it spicy)<br><br>Very delish and satisfying. We took it to a friend&#39;s house who is nearby so we can eat safely.

Excellent fresh and juicy vietnamese sandwiches! It&#39;s a small hole in a wall with 4-5 tables, shelf of snacks and at least 2 drink coolers. It has the feel of a chinese take out joint. I came here twice so far, fell in love with it on my first visit.<br><br>I got #8 grilled pork with pate and asked for it to be spicy. It wasn&#39;t spicy enough for me but has a kick. My hubby usually get #1 which is the most popular- ham &amp; bbq pork with pate. All sandwiches comes with pickled carrots/cucumber and parsley.

comment.text: My favorite bahn mi place!! Great service, great food, reasonable prices... Avocado Smoothie is a must have!!! Taste the real stuff, not just the milk and sugar...

Crispy yet soft bread, a great combination of butter, pate, head cheese / force meats and wonderful garnishes? All for 6 bucks? I can see why this place is so popular and gets all the rave reviews it gets it really is one of the better Banh Mi&#39;s in the tri-state area. Came here ordered the number one and the lemon ice tea for a nice refreshing drink on a relatively hot day. Notice all the workers here were speaking a mix of Vietnamese and cantonese, which is pretty typical of the Vietnamese speaking population in brooklyn. Everything came out quick and was in and out in approximately 10 minutes here. My only gripe with the sandwich, I though it could have used more meat, but then again everything is better with more meat.

comment.text: Best viet sandwiches in the city. Been going there for over 13 years, and it&#39;s still as good as the first time.
My go to spot for banh mi in sunset park area. My fav are their shredded chicken, or combination banh mi, their viet coffee is pretty good also

Been coming here for many years and this place has always been #1 on my bahn mi list. It&#39;s bread is crunchy and the meat were plentiful. The pate was always on point.<br><br>Sadly, I&#39;d have to drop the ratings to 3 stars cause I couldn&#39;t let myself give them anything lower because they have always been so great in the past. I don&#39;t know if it was due to the pandemic and the ingredients are scarce or the price went up but the amount of proportion of ingredients are way off and very disappointing. I don&#39;t mind that they raised the price but raising the price and cheating on the ingredients is a no no for me. I don&#39;t know if its due to pandemic but I probably won&#39;t go back till maybe after the pandemic to try them again. I&#39;m very sad to have to seek other places for bahn mi but this is not working for me. I gave it multiple tries during this time before considering this post and this time it was just bad.<br><br>Hope things will go back to normal after the pandemic but in the mean time, I hope they stay in business.

comment.text: Although they have other items, the banh Mi and iced coffee combo really hits the spot. #1 is a classic but definitely try out the other ones. I know that people really enjoy the avocado smoothie so that will be on my list for the next time I visit them. The ladies that work there are super sweet and fast, even when it&#39;s busy!<br><br>Also, bring cash!

Quick and Delicious! We both got the Banh Mi Pate Thit Nguoi and we loved it. My friend said this is the best bahn mi place she knows and I&#39;ve never had a ban mi before but I&#39;ll definitely be back!

comment.text: THE BEST BANH MI I&#39;VE EVER HAD! My friend bought me one and kept it in the fridge because I couldn&#39;t get to her that day. The next night she popped it in the air fryer and it is easily the best banh mi I&#39;ve ever had. Crispy on the outside, perfect bread that doesn&#39;t scratch the roof of your mouth. The pate was creamy and NOT gamey, which is an issue I have with a lot of pate. The pickled veggies complimented it super well. I highly recommend this! And all for just $6?! A steal! I didn&#39;t take any pics cause I gobbled the whole thing down asap!

What an awesome no frills space in Sunset. Came here with a group of friends and got the special sandwich, the yucca cake, and mungbean cake. <br><br> Amazing flavorful sandwiches, great snacks, and coffee. Super casual with plenty of space to sit and gather around.

comment.text: Love this place but today&#39;s visit was not as good as before. I been coming here for years and they have the best banh mi. But there&#39;s been a few changes. The sandwich is not as thick and filling as before. Prices went up by .50 cent. There&#39;s partitions up and all the tables and chairs are gone. Business is still great. There was a line when I got there today. The phone was ringing nonstop for customer pick up orders. This place is still cash only. I notice quite a few hipsters. Cashier was not using gloves and did not have a mask on but the ladies making the sandwich did. Cashier is taking the cash and putting the sandwich into the bag and making the drinks too all without gloves and mask. (Just want to update people in regards to covid as I know some people do mind. Not trying to nit pick. Just being honest with what I saw.) Ordered number one $6. Bread was perfectly toasted. I asked for spicy and they always get it right but not today. They were too busy and messed up my sandwich. No jalapeño no spicy sauce. The sandwich was thinner too. I also ordered iced Vietnamese coffee $3.25. Still solid and not as sweet. Still going to keep supporting them. Hopefully next visit will be better.

Came back for chicken thigh over rice $6. The chicken was juicy and flavorful and it came with pickled vegetables and jalapeños side of fish sauce.  I can&#39;t believe how good this is and how affordable this meal is. Portions are generous. They do charge 10 cents for a bag now. Banh mi are the best! The ladies working here are nice.

This is the best Vietnamese banh mi spot in America that I tried so far. Even better then the ones I had in California. It&#39;s authentic  and delicious. Bread is perfectly toasted and filled with head cheese, pate mixed with butter, jalua- Vietnamese ham, pickled carrots, cilantro and I asked for jalapeños. They also have banh beo for only $3.75. Most of the banh mi are only $5.50. Their spring rolls are also delicious. Service is friendly but place is definitely dingy looking but still a great spot for authentic and delicious banh mi.

comment.text: Dude. Hole in the wall, but SO GOOD! My fiancé has been on strike with this place ever since they increased their sandwich prices from $3.50 to $7. But come on! $7 for these heavenly sandwiches!?!? It&#39;s a steal. I usually get their signature bahn me (everything smothered in pate between a nice toasty baguette) the few times we&#39;ve been he&#39;ll ask me if I wanted to share a sandwich, thinking I won&#39;t finish it all. Lol. Get out of here boy. I&#39;ll eat mine AND yours! Their porkchop over rice is pretty yums too, but stick with that bahn mi...you won&#39;t regret it.

photos.altText: Photo of Ba Xuyen - Brooklyn, NY, United States

comment.text: Got the #1. The #3 shredded pork was sold out at 1pm on a Saturday. Maybe thats what I should get next time but I doubt Ill come back here with other great options in the vicinity. The bread to filling ratio was a bit high. I&#39;d rather pay a bit more for the right balance. Was asked if I wanted it spicy which I acknowledged but never tasted any spice or saw red sauce. The hard crust of bread left the roof of my mouth serrated after a couple bites so had to adjust my eating technique. Pretty forgettable bahn mi for me but I&#39;ve had some of the best in highly dense Vietnamese populated towns. Looking at the mainly hipster demographics, not surprised &#34;it&#39;s the best they&#39;ve ever had&#34;. Also got the mung bean cake which was new in texture to me. Not too sweet.

messages.<ol&gt;\n <li&gt;Click <b&gt;:
<ol>
            <li>Click <b>Safari</b> in the Menu Bar at the top of the screen, then <b>Preferences</b>.</li>
            <li>Click the <b>Websites</b> tab, then click <b>Location</b> on the left-hand panel.</li>
            <li>Next to <b>yelp.com</b> in the right-hand panel, change the dropdown to <b>Ask</b> or <b>Allow</b>.</li>
            <li>MacOS may now prompt you to enable Location Services. If it does, follow its instructions to enable Location Services for Safari.</li>
            <li>Close the Settings dialog and refresh the page. Try using Current Location search again.</li>

            If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204690" target="_blank">Safari's support page</a>.

messages.We have noticed suspicious review activi: We have noticed suspicious review activity for this business. This sort of activity can take many forms, including when a number of positive reviews originate from the same IP address or when we've identified reviews resulting from a possible <a href='%{consumerAlertsFAQUrl}'>deceptive review ring</a>. Our <a href='%{recommendedReviewFAQUrl}'>automated recommendation software</a> has taken this suspicious activity into account in choosing which reviews to display, but we wanted to call this to your attention because someone may be trying to artificially inflate the rating for this business.
